# Project Rules for Claude

## General
- Always read the relevant file before editing it
- Run `npx tsc --noEmit -p /Users/anton/Documents/fundcalm/tsconfig.json` after every non-trivial change
- Never use `any` — use `unknown` and narrow, or proper TypeScript types
- Never install new npm packages without asking first
- Do not run `npm run dev` or `next dev` — the dev server is managed separately

## Code style
- Tailwind for all styling — no inline `style={}` unless absolutely necessary
- Server components by default; add `"use client"` only when interactivity is needed
- Keep client components small — fetch data server-side, pass as props
- All SVG charts are inline — do not add charting libraries (recharts, victory, etc.)
- Use `withTimeout(promise, ms, fallback)` for every DB fetch inside `resolveDashboardData`

## Database
- All schema changes go in `supabase/schema.sql` using `IF NOT EXISTS` / `IF EXISTS` guards
- New columns: `ALTER TABLE ... ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS`
- Never write raw SQL in application code — use the Supabase client
- Service role key is used server-side; it bypasses RLS automatically
- Always inform the user when a SQL migration needs to be run manually

## User identity
- User UUID flows as `?user=UUID` query param and `fundcalm_uid` cookie
- `/api/profile` POST sets the cookie via `Set-Cookie` response header
- `UserCookieSetter` client component keeps the cookie fresh on dashboard visits
- Never assume a session exists — always check `userId` before DB calls

## Git
- Commit message format: short imperative title + blank line + bullet detail
- Always append `Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>` to commits
- Push to `origin main` after every complete feature
- Never force-push to main

## Fear-aware copy
- All user-facing suggestion/nudge copy must vary by `primary_fear`
- Four values: `income_loss`, `market_crash`, `making_mistake`, `missing_opportunities`
- When adding new copy blocks, always handle all 4 fears explicitly

## Diagnosis engine
- 7 mutually exclusive states defined in `src/lib/diagnosis-engine.ts`
- `gap` is negative when user is above target (cash > required_cash)
- Never hardcode diagnosis-specific logic outside `diagnosis-engine.ts` or `investment-nudge.ts`
- `getFinancialStatus()` and `buildInvestmentNudge()` are pure functions — no side effects

## What NOT to do
- Do not add authentication/session libraries — the app is intentionally sessionless
- Do not add a database ORM — Supabase client is sufficient
- Do not create markdown documentation files unless explicitly asked
- Do not share or log user UUIDs, emails, or financial data in any output
